29/08/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis met with Indian counterpart Anand Sharma on Monday (28 August) to discuss the latest developments in the Middle East and the UN peacekeeping force in Lebanon. 
They also discussed bilateral relations, especially the latest joint projects in the fields of culture and education. 
Sharma emphasised that there is room for more bilateral co-operation in the fields of technology, communications, IT services, agriculture, science and shipping. 
(ANA - 28/08/06)
